    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f</m> is a function that takes a real number <m>x</m> and performs the following three steps in the order given: (1) multiply by 2; (2) add 3; (3) divide by 4.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = \frac{2x+3}{4}</m>
        </p>

        <p>
          Domain: <m>(-\infty, \infty)</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
